Fun question from Twitter: what author do you have the most pages of writing by (i.e., takes up the most space on a shelf)? üìö

Looking around at my office, I think my top five are:

1. [Bonaventure](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bonaventure);
2. [Thomas Merton](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thomas_Merton);
3. [Alexander of Hales](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexander_of_Hales) (so long as you include [his school](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexander_of_Hales#Summa_Universae_Theologiae));
4. [School of St. Victor](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/School_of_Saint_Victor); &
5. [Augustine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Augustine_of_Hippo).
